# Architecture Rules (Flutter/Dart Monorepo)

Architecture is a **hard constraint**, not a suggestion.

All code must be:
- feature-first
- layer-separated
- dependency-safe
- boundary-enforced
- testable in isolation

---

# 1. Monorepo Structure

## Required Layout

```
eddyscout/
├── apps/
│   └── eddyscout/              # Main Flutter application
├── packages/
│   ├── core/                   # Result type, AppFailure, typedefs
│   ├── design_system/          # Material 3 theme, tokens, shared widgets
│   ├── networking/             # Dio factory + interceptor contracts
│   ├── persistence/            # Key-value and structured storage
│   ├── analytics/              # Analytics client interface
│   ├── routing/                # go_router provider and route assembly
│   ├── localization/           # ARB-based l10n
│   └── features/               # Feature packages
│       ├── conditions/
│       ├── map/
│       └── hydro_routing/
├── tooling/                    # Shared analysis_options, coverage config
├── docs/                       # Governance documentation
└── scripts/                    # Automation scripts
```

---

## Rules

- [ ] every feature lives in its own package under `packages/features/`
- [ ] shared concerns live in dedicated shared packages
- [ ] app shell in `apps/eddyscout/` composes features (bootstrap, routing, provider overrides) — see `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- [ ] new UI lives in feature `presentation/` packages (or routing gate screens); do not add `apps/eddyscout/lib/screens/`

---

# 2. Feature Package Structure

## Required Layout

Each feature MUST follow this internal structure:

```
packages/features/<feature_name>/
├── lib/
│   └── src/
│       ├── presentation/       # Widgets, pages, view models
│       ├── domain/             # Entities, use cases, repository contracts
│       └── data/               # Repository implementations, DTOs, data sources
├── test/
│   └── src/
│       ├── presentation/
│       ├── domain/
│       └── data/
├── pubspec.yaml
└── analysis_options.yaml
```

---

## MUST

- [ ] separate presentation, domain, and data layers where the feature has UI (target layout per `packages/features/_TEMPLATE/`)
- [ ] test structure mirrors lib structure exactly
- [ ] one primary public class per file (private helpers allowed)

## Current repo note

Today, `conditions`, `map`, and `hydro_routing` are **partially layered** (e.g. `map` is mostly data; primary screens live in the app shell). New features SHOULD follow full layering; existing code SHOULD migrate incrementally. See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` § Current implementation status.

---

# 3. Dependency Direction (CRITICAL)

## Architecture Diagram

```
presentation → domain ← data
```

Both presentation and data depend on domain. Domain depends on neither.

---

## Rules

| Layer | May Depend On | MUST NOT Depend On |
|-------|--------------|-------------------|
| `presentation/` | `domain/` | `data/`, other features |
| `domain/` | `core` only | `presentation/`, `data/`, Flutter framework |
| `data/` | `domain/` | `presentation/`, other features |

---

## Call Flow (Runtime)

```
UI → Provider → Domain → Data → External APIs
```

> Dependency direction and call flow are distinct concepts. Dependencies point inward toward domain. Calls propagate outward toward data.

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ domain importing data
- ❌ domain importing presentation
- ❌ domain importing Flutter framework
- ❌ data importing presentation
- ❌ presentation importing data directly
- ❌ any layer importing sibling feature internals

---

# 4. Package Boundary Rules

## Monorepo Isolation

- [ ] `packages/*` MUST NOT import from `apps/*`
- [ ] `apps/*` MUST NOT import from other apps
- [ ] feature packages MUST NOT import sibling feature packages

---

## Cross-Feature Communication

Allowed via:
- shared domain contracts in `packages/core/`
- Riverpod providers
- routing layer (`packages/routing/`)

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ import another feature's internal files
- ❌ share state between features via mutable globals
- ❌ bypass domain contracts for convenience

---

# 5. Layer Responsibilities

## presentation/

- widgets, pages, view-model providers
- reads state from Riverpod providers
- dispatches user intent to domain layer
- NO I/O, NO business logic, NO data fetching

---

## domain/

- entities, repository interfaces, use cases
- pure Dart (no Flutter framework dependencies)
- defines contracts that data layer implements
- NO framework deps, NO I/O

---

## data/

- repository implementations, DTOs, data sources
- handles all I/O (network, storage, platform channels)
- maps DTOs ↔ entities
- implements domain repository interfaces

---

# 6. File Organization Rules

## Naming

| Element | Convention |
|---------|-----------|
| Files | `snake_case.dart` |
| Classes | `PascalCase` |
| Variables / functions | `camelCase` |
| Constants | `camelCase` |
| Enum values | `camelCase` |
| Private members | `_camelCase` |

---

## Barrel Files

- [ ] `<package>.dart` exports only public API
- [ ] internal `src/` files are not directly importable by other packages
- [ ] generated files colocated with source files

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ expose internal implementation via barrel files
- ❌ import `src/` paths from other packages
- ❌ place multiple unrelated public classes in one file

---

# 7. Shared Package Rules

## core/

- `Result<T, AppFailure>` type
- shared typedefs and constants
- zero Flutter dependency

---

## design_system/

- Material 3 theme, color scheme, spacing tokens
- shared widgets (buttons, cards, scaffolds)
- typography definitions

---

## networking/

- Dio factory and interceptor contracts
- retry/timeout policy implementation
- NO feature-specific API logic

---

## persistence/

- key-value storage abstraction
- structured storage interfaces
- NO feature-specific persistence logic

---

## routing/

- `RoutePaths`, `resolveAppRedirect`, and `goRouterProvider` in `packages/routing/`
- typed routes and screen binding in `apps/eddyscout/lib/routing/app_routes.dart`
- app overrides via `buildAppProviderOverrides()` in `apps/eddyscout/lib/bootstrap/`
- platform/token redirects stay feature-agnostic via injectable launch-id validation

---

# 8. Async & Error Boundaries

## Package Boundaries

- [ ] new I/O at package boundaries SHOULD return `Future<Result<T, AppFailure>>` (type lives in `packages/core/`)
- [ ] never throw exceptions across package boundaries in new code
- [ ] wrap external exceptions in `AppFailure` when adopting `Result`

---

## UI Layer

- [ ] use `AsyncValue` from Riverpod for all async state
- [ ] handle loading, error, and data states
- [ ] never show raw exception strings to users

---

# 9. Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO)

## MUST NOT

- place business logic inside widgets
- create cross-feature imports
- violate dependency direction
- put I/O in domain layer
- import `data/` from `presentation/`
- use mutable shared state
- create "god" packages that depend on everything
- bypass domain contracts for direct data access
- mix feature code into shared packages

